tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review: In my Doctor was abe identify exact root and star working from Day one which gave relief which was troubling for week.

I contacted the clinic for infection in third molar (wisdom tooth) as I wanted to get the tooth extracted. I was given an appointment and upon inquiring for charges I was told that Doctor will check first and then discuss the same. So I meet the doctor who works for Dr. Eisha Kathuria (name not mentioned on the prescription/letter head). Upon checking my 3 year old OPG(as this was my second extraction) I was told we are ready to remove the tooth. As this was my second, I was aware of the procedure so I asked the doctor why they are not going to treat the infection first as this is going to be invasive(surgical)? I was told that tooth can be removed now. I went for it as I could not bear the pain. Post the procedure, I was handed over a bill of 5200/-. When disputed as it was not communicated, Dr. Eisha was kind enough to give a discount of 1000/-.
This procedure was done in June or July 2016. Stitches were removed on time and I was told that recovery is good. For some reason post this procedure, I always felt discomfort in my lower jaw. I have woken up with a clenched jaw and all day everyday till date I feel discomfort. This was reported to the doctor. They did find tissue scarring but I have been telling them I don't feel blood circulation in the jaw. I have felt sudden blood rush in the jaw upon tapping my face which lead to nausea. I have to constantly maintain pout to relax my jaw. I was given some gel and other meds but the issue remains same. I have been exercising my jaw as prescribed but to no changes. I have never visited the doctor again as I will be taking a second opinion by my previous doctor once he's back in India and decide due course of action.

In discomfort
Shilpa Chakarvarti

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Dr Eisha is extremely Professional and I feel extremely lucky to have found her for my Dental needs. Having come to India from Canada I was looking for a good Dental professional here in Delhi while staying at my relatives. She immediately found the root cause of my problems for which I was being made to beat around the bushes in Canada and the cost was unbelievable. Here I have been suggested a very organic way to deal with my problem and I am sure by the end of my second and last sitting I will be better. Koodo’s to Dr Kathuria  and team .
Thank you very much for all your help and support.
Warmest wishes 
Nipun Gosain

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,
review:
Long and tedious sittings but very skillfully handled by the expertise of Dr Eisha with great deal of patience comforting me at every stage of treatment.
Definitely patient friendly doctor besides a good soul who knows her job well n treat you well too.
At last I must say the entire process was more like a high tea to me than a tedious treatment, though tea n snacks replaced by modern sanitized gadgets, in well neat and clean clinic with ever smiling staff.
Jokes apart, it's definitely worth visiting once to feel the difference.
God Bless Dr Eisha and her clinic.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
Very nice arrangment* *********** ***********
Since you have already made your name/reputation in the locality, may like to reduce charges.

I personally feel that doctor's very important job is to treat as many patients as possible. He/She is considered next to God. 

Keeping charges on higher side you attract affluent people only. Even middle/upper middle class people may not afford to take your services.

My good wishes are there with you. Keep it up and try to serve the society at large.

Regards.
Arun Malik
Addl. General  Manager Rlys (Retd)
